The paper deals with the tradeoffs between individual fairness and performance in online advertising, which involves auction mechanisms and allocation of resources. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper also deals with fairness and social implications, which could make it relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
